{
  "texts": [
    "The framework initially identifies nonsensical concepts from the nonsensical statement.",
    "Subsequently, the framework grounds the relevant implicit knowledge based on the concepts and integrates the implicit knowledge to formulate a prompt for generating the explanation Task formulationGiven a nonsensical statement S = [w 1, w 2,..., w n], where w i represents the i-th word and n is the number of words, the task of commonsense explanation generation aims to generate an explanation Y that clarifies why the statement contradicts commonsense knowledge.The challenge is to ensure that the generated explanation Y accurately addresses the specific aspect of the statement S that contradicts commonsense.",
    "For example, given the statement \"My dad grew volleyballs in his garden,\" the explanation would need to highlight that volleyballs are manufactured, not grown.",
    "This task demands the generated explanations that are not only factually accurate but also intuitively aligned with common human understanding.",
    "Framework overviewAs shown in Fig. 2, the proposed TIP framework enhances commonsense explanation generation through two stages: nonsensical concept identification and knowledge-aware prompting."
  ]
}